# Bards begin with their professional path and gain a bonus standard path at levels 5 and 15.
# Clerics begin with their professional path and two Domains appropriate to their god(s). They gain a bonus standard path at levels 1, 7, 13, and 19. If they select additional domains they may expend feats to buy the granted powers that go with them.
# Druids begin with their professional path and gain a bonus standard path at levels 1, 7, 13, and 19.
# Paladins begin with their professional path and gain a bonus standard path at levels 5 and 15.
# Psions begin with 1 standard path and gain a bonus standard path at levels 6, 11, and 16.
# Psychic Warriors begin with 1 standard path and gain a bonus standard path at levels 7 and 13.
# Rangers begin with their professional path and gain a bonus path at levels 5 and 15.
# Sorcerers begin with their professional path and gain a bonus standard path at levels 7 and 14.
# Wilders begin with 1 standard path and gain a bonus standard path at level 11.
# Wizards do not need spell books and do not gain two individual spells per level. They begin with their professional path and gain a bonus standard path at levels 1, 5, 9, 13, and 18. Wizards may also spend their bonus class feats on getting extra paths as well as on metamagic and item creation feats.
